{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Recognise Chagossian community as a distinct category in official UK statistics",
        "additional_details": "Chagossians were removed from the British Indian Ocean Territory in the 1960s\u201370s and share a distinct history, culture and identity. We believe that formal recognition in official UK statistics would ensure coherence across legislation, policy and public administration, including official classification and status.",
        "background": "Many Chagossians are former residents of the British Indian Ocean Territory, removed in the 1960s\u201370s. The UK recognises them as a community while stating there is no permanent population. We call for formal recognition as a distinct ethnic group in UK official statistics.",
